  "model_paragraph": "The pictures compare the materials needed to produce a paper bag and a plastic bag. Overall, producing a paper bag consumes far more raw materials than a plastic one. Making a paper bag uses up 400ml of oil for transport, treble the amount needed for a plastic bag, and it also requires three times as much wood (30g against 10g). However, slightly more water is needed to create a plastic bag (800ml) than a paper bag (600ml), which is the only exception. Looking at the data from a general perspective, the manufacture of paper bags is more resource-intensive.",
